{"first_name":"Mark","last_name":"Richards","permalink":"mark-richards","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/mark-richards","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"markrichards","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"LugIron Software","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"entrepreneur, investor, social-support-communities, social-crm, database-management","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Wed Apr 29 15:27:53 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Mon Dec 07 19:22:58 UTC 2009","overview":"<p>Mark Richards is a entrepreneur and venture investor. He is currently a Founder of LugIron Software and General Partner at Accede Capital Venture Partners. Prevously, Mark was a General Partner at Technology Venture Partners. </p>\n\n<p>Mark is a serial entrepreneur with over 18 years experience in venture-backed software and communications start-ups. He was founder and CEO of London, England based DBMX, a developer of distributed database management software, acquired by IBM in 1997. In 1998 Mark was co-founder and angel investor in Austin , Texas based PointOne Telecommunications. PointOne subsequently raised the largest ever venture round in Texas of over US$155 million to deploy the industry&#8217;s 1st carrier-grade, nationwide VoIP network. In 2001, Mark co-founded and was CEO of Austin, Texas based Metreos Communications, a venture-backed start-up developing leading edge, standards-based, application and media servers that enable Fortune 500 enterprises to deploy truly converged communications services. Metreos was acquired by Cisco Systems for US$28 million in July 2006.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[109,150],"assets/images/resized/0006/8757/68757v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[183,250],"assets/images/resized/0006/8757/68757v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[220,300],"assets/images/resized/0006/8757/68757v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":""},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"Bachelors of Science (Honors)","subject":"Computer Science","institut